The beach is one of the most secluded spots on the island and the cafe holds pride of place at the water’s edge. 

Owners Noel and Sandra Vella are reportedly being paid thousands of pounds in compensation to shut up shop.

Mrs Vella said: ‘I’m not going to make as much had I remained open throughout these months, but at least I’m getting some form of compensation.’

Gozo - which has a population of 31,000 and is a 20-minute ferry ride from the island of Malta, is famous for its rugged landscapes, spectacular coastline and superb diving conditions.

